my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:46:**Phase 3 — Live capture daemon (CCS-015..CCS-021).** `sample_capture_daemon.py` maintains rolling 60-second buffers of contact mic + room mic via JACK input; an interesting-moment detector flags acoustically novel windows; flagged windows get saved to `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` with auto-generated tags (arc phase, mood, time, who-is-in-room, acoustic features); systemd unit keeps the daemon running. End of phase: leaving the daemon running for an hour produces ~10–30 tagged WAV files representing the room's acoustic life.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:59:- Live JACK capture path — contact mic on `system:capture_FL` and room mic on `system:capture_FR` (Scarlett inputs already wired via `cypherclaw-jack.service`).
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:66:- **New** `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py` — rolling-buffer + interesting-moment detector + auto-tagger
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:67:- **New** `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` — keeps the daemon alive across reboots
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:69:- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py` — interesting-moment detector against canned audio
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:103:| CCS-015 | Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. | MUST | T1 | - daemon opens two JACK ports `cypherclaw-capture:in_contact` and `cypherclaw-capture:in_room`<br/>- each maintains a 60-second numpy ring buffer at 48 kHz<br/>- exposes `get_window(source, duration_sec, offset_sec) -> np.ndarray` for the moment-detector to pull recent windows<br/>- handles JACK xruns gracefully (logs, does not crash)<br/>- tests with a synthetic JACK input fixture verify ring-buffer correctness, window extraction, and xrun recovery |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:104:| CCS-016 | Implement interesting-moment detector: novelty (spectral flux) + transient density + RMS thresholds + duration-min/max gating. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::InterestingMomentDetector` pulls 1-second windows every 250 ms<br/>- flags a window when: `spectral_flux > 0.6 * recent_median` AND `rms > -45 dBFS` AND `transient_count >= 2` AND `since_last_capture > 30 sec`<br/>- on flag, expands to a 4–8 second window centered on the flagged sub-window (length proportional to spectral richness)<br/>- thresholds are tunable via env / config<br/>- tests with canned audio fixtures (silence, footsteps, dishwasher hum, music) verify expected flag/no-flag for each |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:105:| CCS-017 | Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → "warm"; narrow-band high-centroid → "metallic"; sustained_amplitude_ratio>0.7 → "sustained"; transient_density>3/sec → "percussive"; pitch_confidence>0.7 → "harmonic"; etc.<br/>- tests verify each heuristic against canned fixtures and that the merged record validates against `SampleRecord` schema |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:106:| CCS-018 | Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::save_capture(window, source, tags) -> SampleRecord` writes WAV with filename pattern `<source>_<YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ>_<arc>_<sampleid>.wav`<br/>- WAV is 24-bit PCM, 48 kHz, peak-normalized to -1 dBFS unless `peak < -30 dBFS` in which case raw is preserved<br/>- record inserted into `index.sqlite` with `gain_db` set to the normalization adjustment<br/>- tests verify file presence, format (24/48), peak-normalize behavior, and DB row |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:107:| CCS-019 | Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` post-song hook calls `sample_capture_daemon::self_quote(score_summary)` when arc_payoff > 0.6 AND click_count == 0 AND mode != working_ambience<br/>- daemon captures from `SuperCollider:out_1` (via `system:capture_X` after a small JACK loopback connection it manages itself) the 4-second window centered on the moment of peak rolling_peak during the song<br/>- saves to `samples/self/` with `arc_phase`, `mood`, `mode`, and a `self_quote_source_song_id` extra tag<br/>- tests with a mock self-listener stream and arc-payoff fixture verify trigger condition, capture window, and tag propagation |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:108:| CCS-020 | Add systemd unit `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` that runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` with `Restart=always`, dependent on `cypherclaw-jack.service`. | MUST | T2 | - unit file at `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`<br/>- `User=user`, `LimitMEMLOCK=infinity`, `ExecStart=/home/user/cypherclaw/.venv/bin/python3 /home/user/cypherclaw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py`<br/>- `After=cypherclaw-jack.service`, `Requires=cypherclaw-jack.service`<br/>- enabled on boot via `cypherclaw_boot.sh`<br/>- daemon survives a 30-minute soak test with simulated JACK xruns |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:109:| CCS-021 | Implement TDD-grade test fixtures with canned 1-second audio windows representing each detector branch (silence, footsteps, dishwasher, music, dogs, transient cluster) for fast deterministic CI. | MUST | T1 | - `my-claw/tests/fixtures/sample_capture/` directory with WAV fixtures<br/>- `test_sample_capture_daemon.py` exercises each fixture against the detector and asserts expected flag<br/>- fixtures are short (≤2 s) and committed to repo so CI does not need real JACK<br/>- documented as the way to add new detector cases |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:112:| CCS-024 | When a human plays the MIDI keyboard or Theramini for >5 seconds during a song, capture that input phrase to `samples/keyboard/` or `samples/theramini/` with full tagging. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py` listens for keyboard/theramini activity via existing state files (`/tmp/midi_keyboard_activity.json`, `/tmp/theramini_state.json`)<br/>- on >5-second sustained play, captures the corresponding window from the appropriate JACK input<br/>- tags include `human_player` (e.g. `anthony` if face_recognition supports it, else `unknown`), `instrument` (`midi_keyboard` / `theramini`), and the inferred key the human played in<br/>- tests verify trigger threshold, source routing, and tag inclusion |
