,\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:38.152Z\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1776398737913_0\",\"status\":\"success\",\"output\":\"Command exited with code: 1\"}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:41.495Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I'll list all the files in `src/cy\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:41.512Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"pherclaw/render/` to get a complete view of the rendering directory's structure and ensure no relevant files were missed.\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:41.525Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"\\n\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:41.568Z\",\"tool_name\":\"list_directory\",\"tool_id\":\"list_directory_1776398741568_0\",\"parameters\":{\"dir_path\":\"src/cypherclaw/render\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:41.710Z\",\"tool_id\":\"list_directory_1776398741568_0\",\"status\":\"success\"}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:43.409Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I'\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:43.423Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"ll examine `features.py` to see if it contains any information that might be relevant to the `PerformanceIntent` or\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:43.440Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\" the call-response rule implementation.\\n\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:43.481Z\",\"tool_name\":\"read_file\",\"tool_id\":\"read_file_1776398743481_0\",\"parameters\":{\"file_path\":\"src/cypherclaw/render/features.py\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:43.602Z\",\"tool_id\":\"read_file_1776398743481_0\",\"status\":\"success\",\"output\":\"\"}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:46.594Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I'll now create the verification report, as I'm confident in the correctness\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:49.339Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\" of the Lead Agent's implementation within the current codebase.\\n\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:49.510Z\",\"tool_name\":\"write_file\",\"tool_id\":\"write_file_1776398749510_0\",\"parameters\":{\"content\":\"# Verification Report — T-024 @20260416t181925z-verify.md\\n\\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\\n**Date:** 2026-04-17\\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\\n- `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/call_response.py`\\n- `tests/test_call_response.py`\\n- `src/cypherclaw/render/events.py`\\n- `src/cypherclaw/render/role_gate.py`\\n- `my-claw/tools/daemon.py`\\n- `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`\\n\\n## Correctness\\nThe implementation of R11 Call-Response Gating correctly transforms the follower's phrase shape based on the leader's realized performance. The logic in `_descend_from_apex` and `_fill` accurately reflects the requirements for complementarity and filling. Specifically:\\n- When the leader is building (`is_building=True`), the follower's amplitude is reduced and its contour apex is inverted to complement the leader.\\n- When the leader is pausing (`is_pausing=True`), the follower's amplitude is boosted and its contour apex is reinforced to fill the gap.\\n- Role metadata (`leader`, `follower`, `solo`, `tacet`) is correctly parsed and respected, with the rule only applying to voices explicitly tagged as followers.\\n\\n## Completeness\\nThe task is complete according to the acceptance criteria:\\n- `CallResponseRule` implemented in `render/rules/call_response.py`.\\n- Correct transformations for building and pausing states.\\n- Metadata role parsing covers all required keys and values.\\n- Comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_call_response.py` verifies both functional behavior and role-based filtering.\\n\\n## Consistency\\nThe implementation is consistent with other \\\"Tier 1\\\" render rules in `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/` (e.g., `phrase_arch.py`, `articulation.py`). It uses the shared `Event` data model and follows the `role_is_eligible` contract established in `role_gate.py`. Although `PerformanceIntent` was mentioned in the spec, it is not yet present in the codebase (targeted for T-030), and the use of the `Event` model for these transformations is the correct adaptation for the current project state.\\n\\n## Security\\nNo security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices were introduced. The implementation consists of pure-function mathematical transformations on local data structures.\\n\\n## Quality\\nThe code quality is high, with clear documentation, clean dataclass abstractions, and robust role-parsing logic. The tests use Pearson correlation to verify complementarity, which is a rigorous approach for validating musical behavior.\\n\\n## Issues Found\\n- None.\\n\\n## Verdict: PASS\\n\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\nThe implementation successfully realizes the call-response gating requirement. The adaptation to use the `Event` model in the absence of `PerformanceIntent` is appropriate. Recurring hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` were also verified to be satisfied in the current daemon startup paths.\\n\",\"file_path\":\"sdp/verification/t-024 @20260416t181925z-verify.md\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:49.677Z\",\"tool_id\":\"write_file_1776398749510_0\",\"status\":\"success\"}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:55.470Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I've completed the verification report and will now commit it to the repository as instructed.\\n\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:55.507Z\",\"tool_name\":\"run_shell_command\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1776398755507_0\",\"parameters\":{\"command\":\"git add \\\"sdp/verification/t-024 @20260416t181925z-verify.md\\\" && git commit -m \\\"verify(T-024@20260416T181925Z): independent verification pass — PASS\\\"\",\"description\":\"Committing the verification report.\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:56.280Z\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1776398755507_0\",\"status\":\"success\",\"output\":\"[feat/graceful-degradation e05d4ce] verify(T-024@20260416T181925Z): independent verification pass — PASS\\n 1 file changed, 41 insertions(+)\\n create mode 100644 sdp/verification/t-024 @20260416t181925z-verify.md\"}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:58.342Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"The verification of Task T-024 is now\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:58.357Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\" complete, and the implementation of the call-response gating rule has been confirmed as correct and consistent with the project's requirements.\\n\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:58.406Z\",\"tool_name\":\"run_shell_command\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1776398758406_0\",\"parameters\":{\"command\":\"git status\",\"description\":\"Final check of git status.\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-17T04:05:58.769Z\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1776398758406_0\",\"status\":\"success\",\"output\":\"On branch feat/graceful-degradation\\nYour branch is ahead of 'origin/feat/graceful-degradation' by 199 commits.\\n  (use \\\"git push\\\" to publish your local commits)\\n\\nChanges not staged for commit:\\n  (use \\\"git add <file>...\\\" to update what will be committed)\\n  (use \\\"git restore <file>...\\\" to discard changes in working directory)\\n        modified:   progress.md\\n        modified:   sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T181925Zb_1776395654.log\\n        modified:   sdp/logs/Verify_T-021_20260416T181925Zb_1776395753.log\\n        modified:   sdp/notifications.log\\n        modified:   sdp/run-